reviews_data.review_text: Very clean and very caffeine knowledgeable & oriented.  Some vagrants outside panhandling from those who spend $10 on a cup Joe.

I've been a loyal QCG patron for years and always loved the variety of vegan options available. While the menu has clearly changed, and some of my favorites seem to have been removed, it's promising that I still see a few vegan BYO and wrap options that I plan to try in the future.

The biggest disappointment for me has been with the baked goods and pastries. This was always an area where I felt QCG excelled in providing vegan options, and it was always nice to stop in for a chai and a muffin on the way to work. When new management took over, it seems they stopped sourcing baked goods from Whisk & Wood, and after several weeks of no baked goods at all, they appear to be restocked, just with no vegan options. Because of the lack of vegan baked goods and being out of chai, I unfortunately walked out without purchasing anything on my visit this morning. I hope the new managers reconsider offering baked goods for their vegan customers who would like to continue to support a local favorite.

The food and coffee are pretty terrible. I don’t know how people actually come here for that. I do like the atmosphere for getting work done as it’s close to my job, but I wouldn’t recommend spending a lot of money here.

reviews_data.review_text: Tragic!!! This was my favorite coffee shop at one point but everything changed. I seen a regular come in the other day and the owner and the staff were down right rude and disrespectful to him. I’ve seen this guy come for years and bring people and they had no regard for him at all . The food is different, the energy is bad, the servers have attitudes and the so called new owner is very condescending and doesn’t seem to care at all.

This place used to be great but isn’t the same since they came under new management. I’ve witnessed as a regular came in and was severely miss treated by staff and the manager after asking for agave in his tea… you heard that right.
The customer didn’t raise his voice but the manager was condescending and was clapping talking about how he had just got there but never seen this regular who I’ve seen bring other people in, thus additional business. Smh. Do better, this instance and others have made me lose faith in my once adored coffee shop.
reviews_data.owner_answer: We are taking this feedback seriously and making changes for the better, I promise you that.  I hope you consider another visit and keep the feedback coming.

reviews_data.review_text: Go for the coffee NOT the food. Overall, the staff and atmosphere were great, my latte was very good, our Mango smoothie was good, and the food was poor. We had the bacon, egg, and cheese on an everything bagel (only the filling was edible, the bagel was terrible) and the Belgian waffles. The waffles were not good and not fresh.

Took almost an hour to get our food. It ended up being very wrong. We had somewhere to be and couldn't wait another hour for it to be fixed. No manager there, so they couldn't refund it. They offered tokens? (Store credit). We aren't from the area. We ended up just having to take the food and deal with it.

New and Improved! I've lived in the apartments above Queen City Grounds for several years, so this has been my go to location. New ownership/management has taken over and it really shows. The food is better, staff seems more organized, and the atmosphere is even better than before. Highly recommend if you're in the area! Also, the penny wall in the bathroom is awesome!

Since new management/ownership has taken over my go to coffee spot is not the same. Wait times are too long it took over 20 minutes to get a single latte. I know this is due to high turnover and training new individuals but it seems no one is helping these new workers be able to manage multiple orders. My wrap was basically empty and fell apart when I picked it up. I used to love their pastries especially the cinnamon roll but for the past few weeks they have not had any pastries. Multiple times I have gone in and they have been out of whole and oat milk as well as food in the back. It is not the workers fault. New management needs to do better. I’m disappointed and hopeful they can pull through and make a come back.
Splendid coffee & some great food options

reviews_data.review_text: We arrived at this coffee shop 10 minutes after they opened. The young man behind the counter informed us that they were running behind ( no one there but as at the time) and would be with us shortly. We were okay with this as we weren’t in a hurry. 22 minutes later they were ready to take our coffee order . We ordered drip coffee and bagels. Coffee was served quickly but the bagels took another 25 minutes. The young man defensively explained that they were “ extremely backed up”. The staff stood around behind the counter making no attempts to speed service along or reassure the by now, 4 customers in the restaurant. The food and coffee are mediocre, but the defensiveness , inability to be accountable , and the overwhelming “ we don’t care” attitude from staff particularly the young man,will keep us from coming back. At one point this young man stated “ I hate people” when someone asked about their food .Not a good place to visit .
reviews_data.owner_answer: Hi Sarah - I apologize for your poor experience.  This doesn’t not represent our core values one bit.  I will look into this interaction further and take any necessary actions.  Please email me direct at matt@queencitygrounds.com and I will refund your order.

reviews_data.review_text: NEVER AGAIN… I came to this restaurant after searching for “BEST VEGAN BREAKFAST” in Charlotte, NC, and when we arrived the cashier said almost everything here can be made vegan. We ordered a “VEGAN” MAPLE SAUSAGE EGG AND CHEESE SANDWICH. The cashier brought our food to the table, and we started to eat. A bite or two into the sandwich and we noticed that it tasted and looked JUST LIKE real MEAT. I brought the sandwiches back to the counter, and asked the manager were these VEGAN, because they taste like meat. He said almost verbatim “WE DIDN’T HAVE ANY MORE VEGAN SAUSAGE, SO WE JUST GAVE IT TO YOU THE REGULAR WAY”. I was applaud, and extremely disappointed they gave us PORK and no one apologized or tried to accommodate for our experience. I tried to stomach it, and continue eating my side of grits, but started throwing up midway. I’ve been vegan for 15 years, my wife 4 years, and my 8 year old son for his whole life. I must say this is the WORST EXPERIENCE I’VE HAD.

Authentic coffee! They housed an area with local beers. Most days I drop by for an iced latte with extra shot and lavender.. some days I do for sour beer!

Edit after living in Charlotte for over 3 years: This has become my number one coffee place in the entire of NC! Everywhere I go I make sure to get coffee and nothing beats QCG! The best and most consistent good coffee. Today I got one of their seasonal drinks (pictured: Lavender Lemonade) and I can’t believe I’ve been sleeping on it! Burritto You Want is my ultimate favorite food they serve; their Chicken and Waffles are good too!

I can’t recommend this place enough especially if you’re a coffee snob like me!

reviews_data.review_text: I truthfully feel this could be so much better and probably is other days but I went yesterday 6.7.24 and to start the wrong menu was up despite it was a little after 4pm and there were multiple people in there. Once we started to order she was like oh wrong menu were not offering that menu it's after 3 pm yeah it's after 4pm. Then proceeded to tell us a multitude of things we couldn't order off the menu. She named everything fried it seems plus all flate breads. You got coffee and a burger to choose from at this point. She wasn't rude per-say but she wasn't plesant either seemed very annoyed to be there. I will give credit to the burger being good and the coffee tasting good.  However, I don't recommend and I'll not be returning either. If I want to pay almost 70$ for that type of service I'll at the least go where I have menu option or better yet a better attitude to make up for having nothing. Attitude means a lot to me bc customer service is rather worth a bad spot over great food and horrible service.
reviews_data.owner_answer: Unacceptable!  Please email me directly at matt@queencitygrounds.com and I will do what I can to make this right.  I’m sorry you had a negative experience; we pride ourselves on good customer service and this will be addressed.   We have been experiencing some equipment issues we’re working to resolve (which has handcuffed our menu temporarily) but that is no excuse for poor service.  Hopefully we can win you back!

reviews_data.review_text: The place was very nice and clean. This was our first time visiting. They were out of cold brew, the vanilla latte wasn’t great and I was surprised how long our food took and the portion sizes for the price. I think the portion size was perfect BUT the prices were definitely too high. There are many amazing coffee shops with great food here in Charlotte to choose from. $77 (including tip) for 4 drinks, 2 wraps, avocado toast and a grilled cheese.

Overall, I enjoyed my time at Queen City Grounds , but I have to give it four out of five stars because I ordered food and I wanted my pastry warmed up, but the oven was broken and also I sat inside and there were multiple flies and they were bothering me so I just didn’t really enjoy the atmosphere that much but obviously there’s only so much they can do to control that.

reviews_data.review_text: One of the highlights of my day! Food is so good, employees are super nice. Just a lovely neighborhood shop!
reviews_data.owner_answer: Thanks Wendy!  Hope to highlight your days for years to come!

reviews_data.review_text: On Saturday, i went there for a coffee. I got my coffee and sat inside. All of a sudden, water poured on me and my wife. We got wet and my coffee ruined. A tap broke on their counter. Anyways, i clean up myself and returned my coffee, they didn’t apologize at all, very indifferent to what happened. They said they cannot make new coffee because of the broken tap, but they will refund. She went to the computer and said it is refunded. But that was a pure lie. Horrible horrible horrible disrespectful crazy service.

It was a little chaotic when that rinser exploded but that doesn’t excuse poor service/communication. If you can email me at matt@queencitygrounds.com with some details of your order, I will get you squared away.

reviews_data.review_text:
Check your orders before you leave!!
I ordered the burrito with everything that comes with it but I added sausage. I checked my bag before I left but unfortunately it’s hard to see what’s in a burrito unless you open it all the way up. When I got home the only thing the burrito had in it was egg, pico, avocado, cheese and spinach… where is the meat??? No bacon that already suppose to come on it. And I paid extra for sausage… no sausage. It’s a vegan burrito basically which I didn’t order and was charged for the extras. It was missing sauce as well. I’m not sure how you ignore an entire order and make it how you want? I called up there 3 times and of course nobody answered. There’s other spots I normally go to but I wanted to try something new. That’s on me. And I won’t make that mistake again. Pay attention to the orders that come in.
reviews_data.owner_answer: Apologies for the mistake.  I will discuss with the staff, I’m sure it wasn’t done intentionally.  You can email me at matt@queencitygrounds.com with your name and last 4 digits of card used and I will refund the order.  During peak hours it can be difficult to answer phones but we will work on this nevertheless.  We always do our best to reconcile any mistakes and win back anyone who is dissatisfied.  Hopefully you will give us another chance.

reviews_data.review_text: Food & Coffee are all delicious. Subtracting stars due to the wait time that I have every single time I go here. I’ve been here three times now and have waited for my simple food order for 30 mins plus each time. I only order a bacon, egg, & cheese or the grits. So if you are willing to wait a long time for good food, then this is your place! it is located near my office so I will definitely be back but I recommend placing an order online :)

I enjoyed my caramel latte with turmeric agave. I did not taste the food but it look really good and I will be back as they offer breakfast and lunch.

reviews_data.review_text:
Redemption!!! I have been living nearby for a while now. A few months ago, I received poor service and I had written Queen City Grounds off. Tonight we needed a coffee and decided to give it another shot, we were very pleased!

Ben saved the day when he helped us out! He made us feel welcomed and helped us decide what to order. We're not coffee experts, but he didn't care about that, he helped us without judgement. Ben was just an all around pleasure, we really enjoyed talking with him. We already plan to visit him again tomorrow!

After ordering, I enjoyed one of the best latte's ever. I am so glad to see that Queen City Grounds has improved their staff. It is so nice to feel welcome when visiting the neighborhood coffee shop. I'm hoping this could our spot, maybe even our home away from home!

The biggest disappointment for me has been with the baked goods and pastries. This was always an area where I felt QCG excelled in providing vegan options, and it was always nice to stop in for a chai and a muffin on the way to work. When new management took over, it seems they stopped sourcing baked goods from Whisk & Wood, and after several weeks of no baked goods at all, they appear to be restocked, just with no vegan options. Because of the lack of vegan baked goods and being out of chai, I unfortunately walked out without purchasing anything on my visit this morning. I hope the new managers reconsider offering baked goods for their vegan customers who would like to continue to support a local favorite.

New and Improved! I've lived in the apartments above Queen City Grounds for several years, so this has been my go to location. New ownership/management has taken over and it really shows. Since new management/ownership has taken over my go to coffee spot is not the same. Wait times are too long it took over 20 minutes to get a single latte. The staff stood around behind the counter making no attempts to speed service along or reassure the by now, 4 customers in the restaurant. reviews_data.review_text: NEVER AGAIN… I came to this restaurant after searching for “BEST VEGAN BREAKFAST” in Charlotte, NC, and when we arrived the cashier said almost everything here can be made vegan. We ordered a “VEGAN” MAPLE SAUSAGE EGG AND CHEESE SANDWICH. The cashier brought our food to the table, and we started to eat. A bite or two into the sandwich and we noticed that it tasted and looked JUST LIKE real MEAT. I brought the sandwiches back to the counter, and asked the manager were these VEGAN, because they taste like meat. He said almost verbatim “WE DIDN’T HAVE ANY MORE VEGAN SAUSAGE, SO WE JUST GAVE IT TO YOU THE REGULAR WAY”. I was applaud, and extremely disappointed they gave us PORK and no one apologized or tried to accommodate for our experience. I tried to stomach it, and continue eating my side of grits, but started throwing up midway. I’ve been vegan for 15 years, my wife 4 years, and my 8 year old son for his whole life. I must say this is the WORST EXPERIENCE I’VE HAD.
